this might mean that the User will not be able to seek redress under its own jurisdiction‚Äôs privacy laws.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>THE USERS RIGHTS &amp; CONTROL OF PERSONAL INFORMATION</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>Choice and consent:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>By providing personal information, the User consents to the owner(s) of the Website collecting, holding, using and disclosing its personal information in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</li>\r\n 	<li>If a User is under 16 years of age, the User must have, and warrant to the extent permitted by law, that he/she has a parent or legal guardian‚Äôs permission to access and use the Website and they (the parents or legal guardians) have consented to the User providing the Website with personal information.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User does not have to provide personal information; however, the User must be aware that should they refuse, it may affect the use of this Website or the products and/or services offered on or through it.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Information from third parties:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Should the Website receive personal information about a User from a third party, this information will be protected in accordance with this Privacy Policy.</li>\r\n 	<li>If the User is a third party providing personal information about somebody else, the User represents and warrants that he/she/it has such person‚Äôs consent to provide this personal information.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Restrict:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The User may choose to restrict the collection or use of personal information.</li>\r\n 	<li>Should the User have previously agreed to the use of personal information for direct marketing purposes, the User may change his/her mind at any time by contacting the owner(s) of the Website.</li>\r\n 	<li>Should the User ask for a restriction or limitation on personal information which is processed, the owner(s) of the Website may inform the restriction effects on the Users use of the Website or products and services.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Access and data portability:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The User may request details of the personal information that is being held.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User may request a copy of the personal information that the owner(s) of the Website hold.</li>\r\n 	<li>Where possible, the owner(s) of the Website will provide this information in CSV format or other easily readable machine format.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User may request that personal information be erased.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User may also request that this information be passed to another third party.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Correction:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Should the User believe that any information is inaccurate, out of date, incomplete, irrelevant or misleading, the User may contact the owner(s) of the Website to update or correct the information held.</li>\r\n 	<li>The owner(s) of the Website will take all reasonable steps to correct any information found to be inaccurate, incomplete, misleading or out of date.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Notification of data breaches:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The owner(s) of the Website undertake to comply with the regulations and laws applicable, in respect of any data breach.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Complaints:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Should the User believe that the owner(s) of the Website have breached any relevant data protection law and wish to make a complaint, please contact the owner(s) of the Website and provide full details of the alleged breach.</li>\r\n 	<li>The owner(s) of the Website undertake to promptly investigate all complaints, and respond in writing, setting out the outcome of the investigation and the steps taken to address such complaints.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User shall have the right to contact a regulatory body or data protection authority in relation to its complaint.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>Unsubscribe:¬†</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>To unsubscribe from the Website‚Äôs e-mail database or opt-out of communications (including marketing communications), the User is asked to please contact the owner(s) of the Website or opt-out using the opt-out facilities provided in the communication.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>COOKIES</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The Website uses ‚Äúcookies‚Äù to collect information about the User and its activity.</li>\r\n 	<li>Please refer to the Cookie Policy on the Website for more information.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>BUSINESS TRANSFERS</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Should the Website or its assets be acquired, or in the unlikely event that the owner(s) of the Website go out of business or enter bankruptcy, User data, along with other assets, would be transferred to any parties who acquire the Website.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User acknowledges that such transfers may occur, and that any parties who acquire the Website and/or its owner(s) may continue to use the personal information according to this Privacy Policy.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>LIMITS OF OUR POLICY</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>This Website may link to external sites and/or third-party sites which are not operated or controlled by the owner(s) of this Website.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User acknowledges that the owner(s) of the Website have no control over the content and policies of those sites, and therefore cannot accept any responsibility or liability whatsoever for any third-party privacy practices.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User is urged to fully read all legal documents listed on any third-party sites he/she may access or be redirected to from this Website.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>AMENDMENTS TO THE PRIVACY POLICY</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>This Privacy Policy may be amended and updated from time to time, without notice, and shall be effective immediately.</li>\r\n 	<li>The amended Privacy Policy shall immediately replace any previous versions on the Website.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User is urged to regularly visit the Website to ascertain whether there have been any updates to the Privacy Policy.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User‚Äôs continued use of the Website will constitute an unequivocal tacit acceptance of the Privacy Policy listed on the Website.</li>\r\n 	<li>Should the User not accept the amended Privacy Policy, the User is to immediately refrain from using and accessing the Website.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2></h2>\r\n<h2><strong>COOKIES POLICY</strong></h2>\r\nThis Policy, read together with all other legal documents on the Website, shall be legally binding on any person or entity who accesses or uses the ¬†<strong>[site_url]</strong>¬†Website (hereinafter referred to as the ‚ÄúWebsite‚Äù). The User shall be bound by all the Terms &amp; Conditions contained herein, as well as any regulations and laws applicable to the particular jurisdiction from which the User accesses the Website from.¬† Users are urged to read the Website‚Äôs Cookies Policy carefully. This Policy shall replace all previous versions.\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li><strong>WHAT IS A COOKIE?</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>A ‚ÄúCookie‚Äù is a small piece of data which the Website stores on the User‚Äôs computer and/or mobile device and is accessed each time the Website is visited.</li>\r\n 	<li>The Website makes the use of Cookies to collect information about the User and its activities while accessing the Website, which may include, where available, the IP address, operating system and browser type used by the User.</li>\r\n 	<li>This information is collected as statistical data about the Website User‚Äôs browsing actions and patterns, and does not identify any individual in particular.</li>\r\n 	<li>For the same reason, the Website may obtain information about the Users general internet usage by using cookies.</li>\r\n 	<li>The User is responsible for ensuring their computer and/or mobile devices settings are correct and can therefore elect to accept or decline cookies.</li>\r\n 	<li>Cookies help the Company improve their Website(s) and/or Application and to deliver better and more personalized service.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>TYPES OF COOKIES AND HOW THEY ARE USED</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Essential Cookies ‚Äì are cookies which are crucial to the User experience of the Website, enabling core functions like user logins, account management, shopping carts and payment processing. These are used to enable certain functions on the Website. This Website uses essential cookies on the site.</li>\r\n 	<li>Performance Cookies ‚Äì are cookies used in the tracking of how the User uses the Website during a visit, without collecting personal information about the User. Typically, this information is anonymous and aggregated with information tracked across all the Website Users, to help companies understand visitor usage patterns, identify and diagnose problems or errors their users may encounter, and make better strategic decisions in improving their audience‚Äôs overall website experience. These cookies may be set by the Website which the User is visiting or by third-party services. This Website uses performance cookies on the site.</li>\r\n 	<li>Functionality Cookies ‚Äì are used in collecting information about the User‚Äôs device and any settings the User may configure on the website which it is visiting (like language and time zone settings). With this information, websites can provide the User with customized enhanced or optimized content and services. These cookies may be set by the website the User is visiting or by third-party services. This Website uses functionality cookies for selected features on the site.</li>\r\n 	<li>Targeting/advertising Cookies ‚Äì are used in determining what promotional content is more relevant and appropriate to the User and its interests. Websites may use them to deliver targeted advertising or limit the number of times a User may see an advertisement. This helps companies improve the effectiveness of their campaigns and the quality of content presented to the User. These cookies may be set by the website which the User is visiting or by third-party services. Targeting/advertising cookies set by third-parties may be used to track the User on other websites that use the same third-party services. This Website uses targeting/advertising cookies on the site.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>THE FUNCTION OF COOKIES</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Cookies enable the Website to:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>Estimate the audience size and usage pattern;</li>\r\n 	<li>Store information about the Users preferences, and therefore customize and optimize the Website according to the Users individual interests;</li>\r\n 	<li>Speed up the Users searches; and</li>\r\n 	<li>Recognize the User when they return to the Website.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n 	<li><strong>THIRD-PARTY COOKIES ON THE WEBSITE</strong>\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The Website may employ third-party companies and individuals on our Website e.g. analytics providers and content partners.</li>\r\n 	<li>The Website will grant these third-parties access to selected information to perform specific tasks on the Users behalf.</li>\r\n 	<li>They may also set third-party cookies in order to deliver the services they are providing.</li>\r\n 	<li>Third-party cookies can be used to track the User on other websites that use the same third-party service.</li>\r\n 	<li>This Website has no control over third-party cookies and therefore their cookies policies are not covered in this Websites Cookie Policy.</li>\r\n 	<li>This Websites third-party privacy promise:\r\n<ol>\r\n 	<li>The Website reviews the privacy policies of all its third-party providers before enlisting their services to ensure their practices align with its own.</li>\r\n 	<li>The Website will never knowingly include third-party services that compromise or violate the privacy of this Webs